{
  "texts": [
    "However, these approaches cannot directly measure subjective phenomenal experience.",
    "Applying such measures meaningfully to assess consciousness in organoids will require comparative validation.",
    "Understanding mind-brain relationships is intertwined with mapping attributes of consciousness to properties of neural systems (Kandel et al., 2013).",
    "However, the precise linkage between mental states and brain activity remains elusive.",
    "Neuroscience depicts the mind as emerging from the collective interactions of billions of neurons that instantiate cognition and consciousness."
  ]
}